      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The new snow and wind slabs are lying on surface hoar in particular on wind-protected shady slopes. Towards its base, the snowpack is faceted and weak. Avalanches can be released in deeper layers very easily. <br/> In addition the wind slabs adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls are capable of being triggered."
      },
